Typealiases.html#/s:6OpenAI5Modela.name: Model
Typealiases.html#/s:6OpenAI5Modela.abstract: Defines all available OpenAI models supported by the library.

Structs/Vector.html#/s:6OpenAI6VectorV16.name: cosineDifference(a:b:)
Structs/Vector.html#/s:6OpenAI6VectorV16.abstract: Returns the difference between two vectors. Cosine distance is defined as 1 - cosineSimilarity(a, b)

Structs/ModerationsResult/Moderation/Cat.name: harassment
Structs/ModerationsResult/Moderation/Cat.abstract: Content that expresses, incites, or promotes harassing language towards any target.

Structs/ModerationsResult/Moderation/Cat.name: harassmentThreatening
Structs/ModerationsResult/Moderation/Cat.abstract: Harassment content that also includes violence or serious harm towards any target.

Structs/ModerationsResult/Moderation/Cat.name: hate
Structs/ModerationsResult/Moderation/Cat.abstract: Content that expresses, incites, or promotes hate based on race, gender, ethnicity, religion, nationality, sexual orientation, disability status, or caste.

Structs/ModerationsResult/Moderation/Cat.name: hateThreatening
Structs/ModerationsResult/Moderation/Cat.abstract: Hateful content that also includes violence or serious harm towards the targeted group.

Structs/ModerationsResult/Moderation/Cat.name: selfHarm
Structs/ModerationsResult/Moderation/Cat.abstract: Content that promotes, encourages, or depicts acts of self-harm, such as suicide, cutting, and eating disorders.

Structs/ModerationsResult/Moderation/Cat.name: selfHarmIntent
Structs/ModerationsResult/Moderation/Cat.abstract: Content where the speaker expresses that they are engaging or intend to engage in acts of self-harm, such as suicide, cutting, and eating disorders.

Structs/ModerationsResult/Moderation/Cat.name: selfHarmInstructions
Structs/ModerationsResult/Moderation/Cat.abstract: Content that encourages performing acts of self-harm, such as suicide, cutting, and eating disorders, or that gives instructions or advice on how to commit such acts.

Structs/ModerationsResult/Moderation/Cat.name: sexual
Structs/ModerationsResult/Moderation/Cat.abstract: Content meant to arouse sexual excitement, such as the description of sexual activity, or that promotes sexual services (excluding sex education and wellness).

Structs/ModerationsResult/Moderation/Cat.name: sexualMinors
Structs/ModerationsResult/Moderation/Cat.abstract: Sexual content that includes an individual who is under 18 years old.

Structs/ModerationsResult/Moderation/Cat.name: violence
Structs/ModerationsResult/Moderation/Cat.abstract: Content that promotes or glorifies violence or celebrates the suffering or humiliation of others.

Structs/ModerationsResult/Moderation/Cat.name: violenceGraphic
Structs/ModerationsResult/Moderation/Cat.abstract: Violent content that depicts death, violence, or serious physical injury in extreme graphic detail.

Structs/ModerationsResult/Moderation/Cat.name: harassment
Structs/ModerationsResult/Moderation/Cat.abstract: Content that expresses, incites, or promotes harassing language towards any target.

Structs/ModerationsResult/Moderation/Cat.name: harassmentThreatening
Structs/ModerationsResult/Moderation/Cat.abstract: Harassment content that also includes violence or serious harm towards any target.

Structs/ModerationsResult/Moderation/Cat.name: hate
Structs/ModerationsResult/Moderation/Cat.abstract: Content that expresses, incites, or promotes hate based on race, gender, ethnicity, religion, nationality, sexual orientation, disability status, or caste.

Structs/ModerationsResult/Moderation/Cat.name: hateThreatening
Structs/ModerationsResult/Moderation/Cat.abstract: Hateful content that also includes violence or serious harm towards the targeted group.

Structs/ModerationsResult/Moderation/Cat.name: selfHarm
Structs/ModerationsResult/Moderation/Cat.abstract: Content that promotes, encourages, or depicts acts of self-harm, such as suicide, cutting, and eating disorders.

Structs/ModerationsResult/Moderation/Cat.name: selfHarmIntent
Structs/ModerationsResult/Moderation/Cat.abstract: Content where the speaker expresses that they are engaging or intend to engage in acts of self-harm, such as suicide, cutting, and eating disorders.

Structs/ModerationsResult/Moderation/Cat.name: selfHarmInstructions
Structs/ModerationsResult/Moderation/Cat.abstract: Content that encourages performing acts of self-harm, such as suicide, cutting, and eating disorders, or that gives instructions or advice on how to commit such acts.

Structs/ModerationsResult/Moderation/Cat.name: sexual
Structs/ModerationsResult/Moderation/Cat.abstract: Content meant to arouse sexual excitement, such as the description of sexual activity, or that promotes sexual services (excluding sex education and wellness).

Structs/ModerationsResult/Moderation/Cat.name: sexualMinors
Structs/ModerationsResult/Moderation/Cat.abstract: Sexual content that includes an individual who is under 18 years old.

Structs/ModerationsResult/Moderation/Cat.name: violence
Structs/ModerationsResult/Moderation/Cat.abstract: Content that promotes or glorifies violence or celebrates the suffering or humiliation of others.

Structs/ModerationsResult/Moderation/Cat.name: violenceGraphic
Structs/ModerationsResult/Moderation/Cat.abstract: Violent content that depicts death, violence, or serious physical injury in extreme graphic detail.

Structs/ModerationsResult/Moderation.htm.name: categories
Structs/ModerationsResult/Moderation.htm.abstract: Collection of per-category binary usage policies violation flags. For each category, the value is true if the model flags the corresponding category as violated, false otherwise.

Structs/ModerationsResult/Moderation.htm.name: categoryScores
Structs/ModerationsResult/Moderation.htm.abstract: Collection of per-category raw scores output by the model, denoting the model’s confidence that the input violates the OpenAI’s policy for the category. The value is between 0 and 1, where higher values denote higher confidence. The scores should not be interpreted as probabilities.

Structs/ModerationsResult/Moderation.htm.name: flagged
Structs/ModerationsResult/Moderation.htm.abstract: True if the model classifies the content as violating OpenAI’s usage policies, false otherwise.

Structs/ModelResult.html#/s:6OpenAI11Mod.name: id
Structs/ModelResult.html#/s:6OpenAI11Mod.abstract: The model identifier, which can be referenced in the API endpoints.

Structs/ModelResult.html#/s:6OpenAI11Mod.name: created
Structs/ModelResult.html#/s:6OpenAI11Mod.abstract: The Unix timestamp (in seconds) when the model was created.

Structs/ModelQuery.html#/s:6OpenAI10Mode.name: model
Structs/ModelQuery.html#/s:6OpenAI10Mode.abstract: The ID of the model to use for this request.

Structs/ImagesResult/Image.html#/s:6Open.name: b64Json
Structs/ImagesResult/Image.html#/s:6Open.abstract: The base64-encoded JSON of the generated image, if response_format is b64_json

Structs/ImagesResult/Image.html#/s:6Open.name: revisedPrompt
Structs/ImagesResult/Image.html#/s:6Open.abstract: The prompt that was used to generate the image, if there was any revision to the prompt.

Structs/ImagesResult/Image.html#/s:6Open.name: url
Structs/ImagesResult/Image.html#/s:6Open.abstract: The URL of the generated image, if response_format is url (default).

Structs/ImagesResult/Image.html.name: Image
Structs/ImagesResult/Image.html.abstract: Represents the url or the content of an image generated by the OpenAI API.

Structs/ImagesQuery.html#/s:6OpenAI11Ima.name: prompt
Structs/ImagesQuery.html#/s:6OpenAI11Ima.abstract: A text description of the desired image(s). The maximum length is 1000 characters for dall-e-2 and 4000 characters for dall-e-3.

Structs/ImagesQuery.html#/s:6OpenAI11Ima.name: model
Structs/ImagesQuery.html#/s:6OpenAI11Ima.abstract: The model to use for image generation.

Structs/ImagesQuery.html#/s:6OpenAI11Ima.name: responseFormat
Structs/ImagesQuery.html#/s:6OpenAI11Ima.abstract: The format in which the generated images are returned. Must be one of url or b64_json.

Structs/ImagesQuery.html#/s:6OpenAI11Ima.name: n
Structs/ImagesQuery.html#/s:6OpenAI11Ima.abstract: The number of images to generate. Must be between 1 and 10. For dall-e-3, only n=1 is supported.

Structs/ImagesQuery.html#/s:6OpenAI11Ima.name: size
Structs/ImagesQuery.html#/s:6OpenAI11Ima.abstract: The size of the generated images. Must be one of 256x256, 512x512, or 1024x1024 for dall-e-2. Must be one of 1024x1024, 1792x1024, or 1024x1792 for dall-e-3 models.

Structs/ImagesQuery.html#/s:6OpenAI11Ima.name: user
Structs/ImagesQuery.html#/s:6OpenAI11Ima.abstract: A unique identifier representing your end-user, which can help OpenAI to monitor and detect abuse.

Structs/ImagesQuery.html#/s:6OpenAI11Ima.name: style
Structs/ImagesQuery.html#/s:6OpenAI11Ima.abstract: The style of the generated images. Must be one of vivid or natural. Vivid causes the model to lean towards generating hyper-real and dramatic images. Natural causes the model to produce more natural, less hyper-real looking images. This param is only supported for dall-e-3.

Structs/ImagesQuery.html#/s:6OpenAI11Ima.name: quality
Structs/ImagesQuery.html#/s:6OpenAI11Ima.abstract: The quality of the image that will be generated. hd creates images with finer details and greater consistency across the image. This param is only supported for dall-e-3.

Structs/ImageVariationsQuery.html#/s:6Op.name: image
Structs/ImageVariationsQuery.html#/s:6Op.abstract: The image to edit. Must be a valid PNG file, less than 4MB, and square.

Structs/ImageVariationsQuery.html#/s:6Op.name: model
Structs/ImageVariationsQuery.html#/s:6Op.abstract: The model to use for image generation. Only dall-e-2 is supported at this time.

Structs/ImageVariationsQuery.html#/s:6Op.name: n
Structs/ImageVariationsQuery.html#/s:6Op.abstract: The number of images to generate. Must be between 1 and 10.

Structs/ImageVariationsQuery.html#/s:6Op.name: responseFormat
Structs/ImageVariationsQuery.html#/s:6Op.abstract: The format in which the generated images are returned. Must be one of url or b64_json.

Structs/ImageVariationsQuery.html#/s:6Op.name: size
Structs/ImageVariationsQuery.html#/s:6Op.abstract: The size of the generated images. Must be one of 256x256, 512x512, or 1024x1024.

Structs/ImageVariationsQuery.html#/s:6Op.name: user
Structs/ImageVariationsQuery.html#/s:6Op.abstract: A unique identifier representing your end-user, which can help OpenAI to monitor and detect abuse.

Structs/ImageEditsQuery.html#/s:6OpenAI1.name: image
Structs/ImageEditsQuery.html#/s:6OpenAI1.abstract: The image to edit. Must be a valid PNG file, less than 4MB, and square. If mask is not provided, image must have transparency, which will be used as the mask.

Structs/ImageEditsQuery.html#/s:6OpenAI1.name: mask
Structs/ImageEditsQuery.html#/s:6OpenAI1.abstract: An additional image whose fully transparent areas (e.g. where alpha is zero) indicate where image should be edited. Must be a valid PNG file, less than 4MB, and have the same dimensions as image.

Structs/ImageEditsQuery.html#/s:6OpenAI1.name: prompt
Structs/ImageEditsQuery.html#/s:6OpenAI1.abstract: A text description of the desired image(s). The maximum length is 1000 characters.

Structs/ImageEditsQuery.html#/s:6OpenAI1.name: model
Structs/ImageEditsQuery.html#/s:6OpenAI1.abstract: The model to use for image generation.

Structs/ImageEditsQuery.html#/s:6OpenAI1.name: n
Structs/ImageEditsQuery.html#/s:6OpenAI1.abstract: The number of images to generate. Must be between 1 and 10.

Structs/ImageEditsQuery.html#/s:6OpenAI1.name: responseFormat
Structs/ImageEditsQuery.html#/s:6OpenAI1.abstract: The format in which the generated images are returned. Must be one of url or b64_json.

Structs/ImageEditsQuery.html#/s:6OpenAI1.name: size
Structs/ImageEditsQuery.html#/s:6OpenAI1.abstract: The size of the generated images. Must be one of 256x256, 512x512, or 1024x1024.

Structs/ImageEditsQuery.html#/s:6OpenAI1.name: user
Structs/ImageEditsQuery.html#/s:6OpenAI1.abstract: A unique identifier representing your end-user, which can help OpenAI to monitor and detect abuse.

Structs/EmbeddingsResult/Embedding.html#.name: embedding
Structs/EmbeddingsResult/Embedding.html#.abstract: The embedding vector, which is a list of floats. The length of vector depends on the model as listed in the embedding guide.

Structs/EmbeddingsQuery.html#/s:6OpenAI1.name: input
Structs/EmbeddingsQuery.html#/s:6OpenAI1.abstract: Input text to embed, encoded as a string or array of tokens. To embed multiple inputs in a single request, pass an array of strings or array of token arrays. The input must not exceed the max input tokens for the model (8192 tokens for text-embedding-ada-002), cannot be an empty string, and any array must be 2048 dimensions or less.

Structs/EmbeddingsQuery.html#/s:6OpenAI1.name: model
Structs/EmbeddingsQuery.html#/s:6OpenAI1.abstract: ID of the model to use. You can use the List models API to see all of your available models, or see our Model overview for descriptions of them.

Structs/EmbeddingsQuery.html#/s:6OpenAI1.name: encodingFormat
Structs/EmbeddingsQuery.html#/s:6OpenAI1.abstract: The format to return the embeddings in. Can be either float or base64.

Structs/EmbeddingsQuery.html#/s:6OpenAI1.name: user
Structs/EmbeddingsQuery.html#/s:6OpenAI1.abstract: A unique identifier representing your end-user, which can help OpenAI to monitor and detect abuse.

Structs/EditsQuery.html#/s:6OpenAI10Edit.name: instruction
Structs/EditsQuery.html#/s:6OpenAI10Edit.abstract: The instruction that tells the model how to edit the prompt.

Structs/EditsQuery.html#/s:6OpenAI10Edit.name: n
Structs/EditsQuery.html#/s:6OpenAI10Edit.abstract: The number of images to generate. Must be between 1 and 10.

Structs/EditsQuery.html#/s:6OpenAI10Edit.name: temperature
Structs/EditsQuery.html#/s:6OpenAI10Edit.abstract: What sampling temperature to use. Higher values means the model will take more risks. Try 0.9 for more creative applications, and 0 (argmax sampling) for ones with a well-defined answer.

Structs/EditsQuery.html#/s:6OpenAI10Edit.name: topP
Structs/EditsQuery.html#/s:6OpenAI10Edit.abstract: An alternative to sampling with temperature, called nucleus sampling, where the model considers the results of the tokens with top_p probability mass. So 0.1 means only the tokens comprising the top 10% probability mass are considered.

Structs/CompletionsQuery.html#/s:6OpenAI.name: prompt
Structs/CompletionsQuery.html#/s:6OpenAI.abstract: The prompt(s) to generate completions for, encoded as a string, array of strings, array of tokens, or array of token arrays.

Structs/CompletionsQuery.html#/s:6OpenAI.name: temperature
Structs/CompletionsQuery.html#/s:6OpenAI.abstract: What sampling temperature to use. Higher values means the model will take more risks. Try 0.9 for more creative applications, and 0 (argmax sampling) for ones with a well-defined answer.

Structs/CompletionsQuery.html#/s:6OpenAI.name: maxTokens
Structs/CompletionsQuery.html#/s:6OpenAI.abstract: The maximum number of tokens to generate in the completion.

Structs/CompletionsQuery.html#/s:6OpenAI.name: topP
Structs/CompletionsQuery.html#/s:6OpenAI.abstract: An alternative to sampling with temperature, called nucleus sampling, where the model considers the results of the tokens with top_p probability mass. So 0.1 means only the tokens comprising the top 10% probability mass are considered.

Structs/CompletionsQuery.html#/s:6OpenAI.name: frequencyPenalty
Structs/CompletionsQuery.html#/s:6OpenAI.abstract: Number between -2.0 and 2.0. Positive values penalize new tokens based on their existing frequency in the text so far, decreasing the model’s likelihood to repeat the same line verbatim.

Structs/CompletionsQuery.html#/s:6OpenAI.name: presencePenalty
Structs/CompletionsQuery.html#/s:6OpenAI.abstract: Number between -2.0 and 2.0. Positive values penalize new tokens based on whether they appear in the text so far, increasing the model’s likelihood to talk about new topics.

Structs/CompletionsQuery.html#/s:6OpenAI.name: stop
Structs/CompletionsQuery.html#/s:6OpenAI.abstract: Up to 4 sequences where the API will stop generating further tokens. The returned text will not contain the stop sequence.

Structs/CompletionsQuery.html#/s:6OpenAI.name: user
Structs/CompletionsQuery.html#/s:6OpenAI.abstract: A unique identifier representing your end-user, which can help OpenAI to monitor and detect abuse.

Structs/ChatStreamResult/Choice/ChoiceLo.name: bytes
Structs/ChatStreamResult/Choice/ChoiceLo.abstract: A list of integers representing the UTF-8 bytes representation of the token. Useful in instances where characters are represented by multiple tokens and their byte representations must be combined to generate the correct text representation. Can be null if there is no bytes representation for the token.

Structs/ChatStreamResult/Choice/ChoiceLo.name: bytes
Structs/ChatStreamResult/Choice/ChoiceLo.abstract: A list of integers representing the UTF-8 bytes representation of the token. Useful in instances where characters are represented by multiple tokens and their byte representations must be combined to generate the correct text representation. Can be null if there is no bytes representation for the token.

Structs/ChatStreamResult/Choice/ChoiceLo.name: topLogprobs
Structs/ChatStreamResult/Choice/ChoiceLo.abstract: List of the most likely tokens and their log probability, at this token position. In rare cases, there may be fewer than the number of requested top_logprobs returned.

Structs/ChatStreamResult/Choice/ChoiceLo.name: content
Structs/ChatStreamResult/Choice/ChoiceLo.abstract: A list of message content tokens with log probability information.

Structs/ChatStreamResult/Choice/ChoiceDe.name: arguments
Structs/ChatStreamResult/Choice/ChoiceDe.abstract: The arguments to call the function with, as generated by the model in JSON format. Note that the model does not always generate valid JSON, and may hallucinate parameters not defined by your function schema. Validate the arguments in your code before calling your function.

Structs/ChatStreamResult/Choice/ChoiceDe.name: name
Structs/ChatStreamResult/Choice/ChoiceDe.abstract: The name of the function to call.

Structs/ChatStreamResult/Choice/ChoiceDe.name: type
Structs/ChatStreamResult/Choice/ChoiceDe.abstract: The type of the tool. Currently, only function is supported.

Structs/ChatStreamResult/Choice/ChoiceDe.name: role
Structs/ChatStreamResult/Choice/ChoiceDe.abstract: The role of the author of this message.

Structs/ChatStreamResult/Choice.html#/s:.name: delta
Structs/ChatStreamResult/Choice.html#/s:.abstract: A chat completion delta generated by streamed model responses.

Structs/ChatStreamResult/Choice.html#/s:.name: finishReason
Structs/ChatStreamResult/Choice.html#/s:.abstract: The reason the model stopped generating tokens.

Structs/ChatStreamResult.html#/s:6OpenAI.name: id
Structs/ChatStreamResult.html#/s:6OpenAI.abstract: A unique identifier for the chat completion. Each chunk has the same ID.

Structs/ChatStreamResult.html#/s:6OpenAI.name: created
Structs/ChatStreamResult.html#/s:6OpenAI.abstract: The Unix timestamp (in seconds) of when the chat completion was created.

Structs/ChatStreamResult.html#/s:6OpenAI.name: systemFingerprint
Structs/ChatStreamResult.html#/s:6OpenAI.abstract: This fingerprint represents the backend configuration that the model runs with. Can be used in conjunction with the seed request parameter to understand when backend changes have been made that might impact determinism.

Structs/ChatResult/CompletionUsage.html#.name: completionTokens
Structs/ChatResult/CompletionUsage.html#.abstract: Number of tokens in the generated completion.

Structs/ChatResult/CompletionUsage.html#.name: totalTokens
Structs/ChatResult/CompletionUsage.html#.abstract: Total number of tokens used in the request (prompt + completion).

Structs/ChatResult/Choice/ChoiceLogprobs.name: bytes
Structs/ChatResult/Choice/ChoiceLogprobs.abstract: A list of integers representing the UTF-8 bytes representation of the token.

Structs/ChatResult/Choice/ChoiceLogprobs.name: bytes
Structs/ChatResult/Choice/ChoiceLogprobs.abstract: A list of integers representing the UTF-8 bytes representation of the token.

Structs/ChatResult/Choice/ChoiceLogprobs.name: topLogprobs
Structs/ChatResult/Choice/ChoiceLogprobs.abstract: List of the most likely tokens and their log probability, at this token position.

Structs/ChatResult/Choice.html#/s:6OpenA.name: message
Structs/ChatResult/Choice.html#/s:6OpenA.abstract: A chat completion message generated by the model.

Structs/ChatResult/Choice.html#/s:6OpenA.name: finishReason
Structs/ChatResult/Choice.html#/s:6OpenA.abstract: The reason the model stopped generating tokens. This will be stop if the model hit a natural stop point or a provided stop sequence, length if the maximum number of tokens specified in the request was reached, content_filter if content was omitted due to a flag from our content filters, tool_calls if the model called a tool, or function_call (deprecated) if the model called a function.

Structs/ChatResult/Choice.html.name: Choice
Structs/ChatResult/Choice.html.abstract: mimic the choices array in the chat completion object

Structs/ChatResult.html#/s:6OpenAI10Chat.name: id
Structs/ChatResult.html#/s:6OpenAI10Chat.abstract: A unique identifier for the chat completion.

Structs/ChatResult.html#/s:6OpenAI10Chat.name: object
Structs/ChatResult.html#/s:6OpenAI10Chat.abstract: The object type, which is always chat.completion.

Structs/ChatResult.html#/s:6OpenAI10Chat.name: created
Structs/ChatResult.html#/s:6OpenAI10Chat.abstract: The Unix timestamp (in seconds) of when the chat completion was created.

Structs/ChatResult.html#/s:6OpenAI10Chat.name: model
Structs/ChatResult.html#/s:6OpenAI10Chat.abstract: The model used for the chat completion.

Structs/ChatResult.html#/s:6OpenAI10Chat.name: choices
Structs/ChatResult.html#/s:6OpenAI10Chat.abstract: A list of chat completion choices. Can be more than one if n is greater than 1.

Structs/ChatResult.html#/s:6OpenAI10Chat.name: systemFingerprint
Structs/ChatResult.html#/s:6OpenAI10Chat.abstract: This fingerprint represents the backend configuration that the model runs with.

Structs/ChatQuery/ChatCompletionToolPara.name: name
Structs/ChatQuery/ChatCompletionToolPara.abstract: The name of the function to be called. Must be a-z, A-Z, 0-9, or contain underscores and dashes, with a maximum length of 64.

Structs/ChatQuery/ChatCompletionToolPara.name: description
Structs/ChatQuery/ChatCompletionToolPara.abstract: The description of what the function does.

Structs/ChatQuery/ChatCompletionToolPara.name: parameters
Structs/ChatQuery/ChatCompletionToolPara.abstract: The parameters the functions accepts, described as a JSON Schema object.

Structs/ChatQuery/ChatCompletionToolPara.name: FunctionParameters
Structs/ChatQuery/ChatCompletionToolPara.abstract: See the guide for examples, and the JSON Schema reference for documentation about the format.

Structs/ChatQuery/ChatCompletionMessageP.name: content
Structs/ChatQuery/ChatCompletionMessageP.abstract: The contents of the tool message.

Structs/ChatQuery/ChatCompletionMessageP.name: role
Structs/ChatQuery/ChatCompletionMessageP.abstract: The role of the messages author, in this case tool.

Structs/ChatQuery/ChatCompletionMessageP.name: toolCallId
Structs/ChatQuery/ChatCompletionMessageP.abstract: Tool call that this message is responding to.

Structs/ChatQuery/ChatCompletionMessageP.name: arguments
Structs/ChatQuery/ChatCompletionMessageP.abstract: The arguments to call the function with, as generated by the model in JSON format. Note that the model does not always generate valid JSON, and may hallucinate parameters not defined by your function schema. Validate the arguments in your code before calling your function.

Structs/ChatQuery/ChatCompletionMessageP.name: name
Structs/ChatQuery/ChatCompletionMessageP.abstract: The name of the function to call.

Structs/ChatQuery/ChatCompletionMessageP.name: id
Structs/ChatQuery/ChatCompletionMessageP.abstract: The ID of the tool call.

Structs/ChatQuery/ChatCompletionMessageP.name: function
Structs/ChatQuery/ChatCompletionMessageP.abstract: The function that the model called.

Structs/ChatQuery/ChatCompletionMessageP.name: type
Structs/ChatQuery/ChatCompletionMessageP.abstract: The type of the tool. Currently, only function is supported.

Structs/ChatQuery/ChatCompletionMessageP.name: role
Structs/ChatQuery/ChatCompletionMessageP.abstract: / The role of the messages author, in this case assistant.

Structs/ChatQuery/ChatCompletionMessageP.name: content
Structs/ChatQuery/ChatCompletionMessageP.abstract: The contents of the assistant message. Required unless tool_calls is specified.

Structs/ChatQuery/ChatCompletionMessageP.name: name
Structs/ChatQuery/ChatCompletionMessageP.abstract: The name of the author of this message. name is required if role is function, and it should be the name of the function whose response is in the content. May contain a-z, A-Z, 0-9, and underscores, with a maximum length of 64 characters.

Structs/ChatQuery/ChatCompletionMessageP.name: toolCalls
Structs/ChatQuery/ChatCompletionMessageP.abstract: The tool calls generated by the model, such as function calls.

Structs/ChatQuery/ChatCompletionMessageP.name: url
Structs/ChatQuery/ChatCompletionMessageP.abstract: Either a URL of the image or the base64 encoded image data.

Structs/ChatQuery/ChatCompletionMessageP.name: detail
Structs/ChatQuery/ChatCompletionMessageP.abstract: Specifies the detail level of the image. Learn more in the

Structs/ChatQuery/ChatCompletionMessageP.name: type
Structs/ChatQuery/ChatCompletionMessageP.abstract: The type of the content part.

Structs/ChatQuery/ChatCompletionMessageP.name: text
Structs/ChatQuery/ChatCompletionMessageP.abstract: The text content.

Structs/ChatQuery/ChatCompletionMessageP.name: type
Structs/ChatQuery/ChatCompletionMessageP.abstract: The type of the content part.

Structs/ChatQuery/ChatCompletionMessageP.name: content
Structs/ChatQuery/ChatCompletionMessageP.abstract: The contents of the user message.

Structs/ChatQuery/ChatCompletionMessageP.name: role
Structs/ChatQuery/ChatCompletionMessageP.abstract: The role of the messages author, in this case user.

Structs/ChatQuery/ChatCompletionMessageP.name: name
Structs/ChatQuery/ChatCompletionMessageP.abstract: An optional name for the participant. Provides the model information to differentiate between participants of the same role.

Structs/ChatQuery/ChatCompletionMessageP.name: content
Structs/ChatQuery/ChatCompletionMessageP.abstract: The contents of the system message.

Structs/ChatQuery/ChatCompletionMessageP.name: role
Structs/ChatQuery/ChatCompletionMessageP.abstract: The role of the messages author, in this case system.

Structs/ChatQuery/ChatCompletionMessageP.name: name
Structs/ChatQuery/ChatCompletionMessageP.abstract: An optional name for the participant. Provides the model information to differentiate between participants of the same role.

Structs/ChatQuery.html#/s:6OpenAI9ChatQu.name: messages
Structs/ChatQuery.html#/s:6OpenAI9ChatQu.abstract: A list of messages comprising the conversation so far

Structs/ChatQuery.html#/s:6OpenAI9ChatQu.name: model
Structs/ChatQuery.html#/s:6OpenAI9ChatQu.abstract: ID of the model to use. See the model endpoint compatibility table for details on which models work with the Chat API.

Structs/ChatQuery.html#/s:6OpenAI9ChatQu.name: frequencyPenalty
Structs/ChatQuery.html#/s:6OpenAI9ChatQu.abstract: Number between -2.0 and 2.0. Positive values penalize new tokens based on their existing frequency in the text so far, decreasing the model’s likelihood to repeat the same line verbatim.

Structs/ChatQuery.html#/s:6OpenAI9ChatQu.name: logitBias
Structs/ChatQuery.html#/s:6OpenAI9ChatQu.abstract: Modify the likelihood of specified tokens appearing in the completion.

Structs/ChatQuery.html#/s:6OpenAI9ChatQu.name: logprobs
Structs/ChatQuery.html#/s:6OpenAI9ChatQu.abstract: Whether to return log probabilities of the output tokens or not. If true, returns the log probabilities of each output token returned in the content of message. This option is currently not available on the gpt-4-vision-preview model.

Structs/ChatQuery.html#/s:6OpenAI9ChatQu.name: maxTokens
Structs/ChatQuery.html#/s:6OpenAI9ChatQu.abstract: The maximum number of tokens to generate in the completion.

Structs/ChatQuery.html#/s:6OpenAI9ChatQu.name: n
Structs/ChatQuery.html#/s:6OpenAI9ChatQu.abstract: How many chat completion choices to generate for each input message. Note that you will be charged based on the number of generated tokens across all of the choices. Keep n as 1 to minimize costs.

Structs/ChatQuery.html#/s:6OpenAI9ChatQu.name: presencePenalty
Structs/ChatQuery.html#/s:6OpenAI9ChatQu.abstract: Number between -2.0 and 2.0. Positive values penalize new tokens based on whether they appear in the text so far, increasing the model’s likelihood to talk about new topics.

Structs/ChatQuery.html#/s:6OpenAI9ChatQu.name: responseFormat
Structs/ChatQuery.html#/s:6OpenAI9ChatQu.abstract: An object specifying the format that the model must output. Compatible with gpt-4-1106-preview and gpt-3.5-turbo-1106.

Structs/ChatQuery.html#/s:6OpenAI9ChatQu.name: seed
Structs/ChatQuery.html#/s:6OpenAI9ChatQu.abstract: This feature is in Beta. If specified, our system will make a best effort to sample deterministically, such that repeated requests with the same seed and parameters should return the same result. Determinism is not guaranteed, and you should refer to the system_fingerprint response parameter to monitor changes in the backend.

Structs/ChatQuery.html#/s:6OpenAI9ChatQu.name: stop
Structs/ChatQuery.html#/s:6OpenAI9ChatQu.abstract: Up to 4 sequences where the API will stop generating further tokens. The returned text will not contain the stop sequence.

Structs/ChatQuery.html#/s:6OpenAI9ChatQu.name: temperature
Structs/ChatQuery.html#/s:6OpenAI9ChatQu.abstract: What sampling temperature to use, between 0 and 2. Higher values like 0.8 will make the output more random, while lower values like 0.2 will make it more focused and deterministic.

Structs/ChatQuery.html#/s:6OpenAI9ChatQu.name: toolChoice
Structs/ChatQuery.html#/s:6OpenAI9ChatQu.abstract: Controls which (if any) function is called by the model. none means the model will not call a function and instead generates a message. auto means the model can pick between generating a message or calling a function. Specifying a particular function via {“type”: “function”, “function”: {“name”: “my_function”}} forces the model to call that function.

Structs/ChatQuery.html#/s:6OpenAI9ChatQu.name: tools
Structs/ChatQuery.html#/s:6OpenAI9ChatQu.abstract: A list of tools the model may call. Currently, only functions are supported as a tool. Use this to provide a list of functions the model may generate JSON inputs for.

Structs/ChatQuery.html#/s:6OpenAI9ChatQu.name: topLogprobs
Structs/ChatQuery.html#/s:6OpenAI9ChatQu.abstract: An integer between 0 and 5 specifying the number of most likely tokens to return at each token position, each with an associated log probability. logprobs must be set to true if this parameter is used.

Structs/ChatQuery.html#/s:6OpenAI9ChatQu.name: topP
Structs/ChatQuery.html#/s:6OpenAI9ChatQu.abstract: An alternative to sampling with temperature, called nucleus sampling, where the model considers the results of the tokens with top_p probability mass. So 0.1 means only the tokens comprising the top 10% probability mass are considered.

Structs/ChatQuery.html#/s:6OpenAI9ChatQu.name: user
Structs/ChatQuery.html#/s:6OpenAI9ChatQu.abstract: A unique identifier representing your end-user, which can help OpenAI to monitor and detect abuse.

Structs/ChatQuery.html#/s:6OpenAI9ChatQu.name: stream
Structs/ChatQuery.html#/s:6OpenAI9ChatQu.abstract: If set, partial message deltas will be sent, like in ChatGPT. Tokens will be sent as data-only server-sent events as they become available, with the stream terminated by a data: [DONE] message.

Structs/AudioTranslationQuery.html#/s:6O.name: file
Structs/AudioTranslationQuery.html#/s:6O.abstract: The audio file object (not file name) translate, in one of these formats: flac, mp3, mp4, mpeg, mpga, m4a, ogg, wav, or webm.

Structs/AudioTranslationQuery.html#/s:6O.name: model
Structs/AudioTranslationQuery.html#/s:6O.abstract: ID of the model to use. Only whisper-1 is currently available.

Structs/AudioTranslationQuery.html#/s:6O.name: responseFormat
Structs/AudioTranslationQuery.html#/s:6O.abstract: The format of the transcript output, in one of these options: json, text, srt, verbose_json, or vtt.

Structs/AudioTranslationQuery.html#/s:6O.name: prompt
Structs/AudioTranslationQuery.html#/s:6O.abstract: An optional text to guide the model’s style or continue a previous audio segment. The prompt should be in English.

Structs/AudioTranslationQuery.html#/s:6O.name: temperature
Structs/AudioTranslationQuery.html#/s:6O.abstract: The sampling temperature, between 0 and 1. Higher values like 0.8 will make the output more random, while lower values like 0.2 will make it more focused and deterministic. If set to 0, the model will use log probability to automatically increase the temperature until certain thresholds are hit.

Structs/AudioTranscriptionQuery.html#/s:.name: file
Structs/AudioTranscriptionQuery.html#/s:.abstract: The audio file object (not file name) to transcribe, in one of these formats: flac, mp3, mp4, mpeg, mpga, m4a, ogg, wav, or webm.

Structs/AudioTranscriptionQuery.html#/s:.name: model
Structs/AudioTranscriptionQuery.html#/s:.abstract: ID of the model to use. Only whisper-1 is currently available.

Structs/AudioTranscriptionQuery.html#/s:.name: responseFormat
Structs/AudioTranscriptionQuery.html#/s:.abstract: The format of the transcript output, in one of these options: json, text, srt, verbose_json, or vtt.

Structs/AudioTranscriptionQuery.html#/s:.name: prompt
Structs/AudioTranscriptionQuery.html#/s:.abstract: An optional text to guide the model’s style or continue a previous audio segment. The prompt should match the audio language.

Structs/AudioTranscriptionQuery.html#/s:.name: temperature
Structs/AudioTranscriptionQuery.html#/s:.abstract: The sampling temperature, between 0 and 1. Higher values like 0.8 will make the output more random, while lower values like 0.2 will make it more focused and deterministic. If set to 0, the model will use log probability to automatically increase the temperature until certain thresholds are hit.

Structs/AudioTranscriptionQuery.html#/s:.name: language
Structs/AudioTranscriptionQuery.html#/s:.abstract: The language of the input audio. Supplying the input language in ISO-639-1 format will improve accuracy and latency.

Structs/AudioSpeechResult.html#/s:6OpenA.name: audio
Structs/AudioSpeechResult.html#/s:6OpenA.abstract: Audio data for one of the following formats :mp3, opus, aac, flac

Structs/AudioSpeechQuery/AudioSpeechVoic.name: AudioSpeechVoice
Structs/AudioSpeechQuery/AudioSpeechVoic.abstract: Encapsulates the voices available for audio generation.

Structs/AudioSpeechQuery/AudioSpeechResp.name: AudioSpeechResponseFormat
Structs/AudioSpeechQuery/AudioSpeechResp.abstract: Encapsulates the response formats available for audio data.

Structs/AudioSpeechQuery.html#/s:6OpenAI.name: input
Structs/AudioSpeechQuery.html#/s:6OpenAI.abstract: The text to generate audio for. The maximum length is 4096 characters.

Structs/AudioSpeechQuery.html#/s:6OpenAI.name: model
Structs/AudioSpeechQuery.html#/s:6OpenAI.abstract: One of the available TTS models: tts-1 or tts-1-hd

Structs/AudioSpeechQuery.html#/s:6OpenAI.name: voice
Structs/AudioSpeechQuery.html#/s:6OpenAI.abstract: The voice to use when generating the audio. Supported voices are alloy, echo, fable, onyx, nova, and shimmer. Previews of the voices are available in the Text to speech guide.

Structs/AudioSpeechQuery.html#/s:6OpenAI.name: responseFormat
Structs/AudioSpeechQuery.html#/s:6OpenAI.abstract: The format to audio in. Supported formats are mp3, opus, aac, and flac.

Structs/AudioSpeechQuery.html#/s:6OpenAI.name: speed
Structs/AudioSpeechQuery.html#/s:6OpenAI.abstract: The speed of the generated audio. Select a value from 0.25 to 4.0. 1.0 is the default.

Structs/ChatQuery.html.name: ChatQuery
Structs/ChatQuery.html.abstract: Creates a model response for the given chat conversation

Structs/ImagesQuery.html.name: ImagesQuery
Structs/ImagesQuery.html.abstract: Given a prompt and/or an input image, the model will generate a new image.

Structs/ModelQuery.html.name: ModelQuery
Structs/ModelQuery.html.abstract: Retrieves a model instance, providing basic information about the model such as the owner and permissioning.

Structs/ModelResult.html.name: ModelResult
Structs/ModelResult.html.abstract: The model object matching the specified ID.

Protocols/OpenAIProtocol.html#/s:6OpenAI.name: completions(query:completion:)
Protocols/OpenAIProtocol.html#/s:6OpenAI.abstract: This function sends a completions query to the OpenAI API and retrieves generated completions in response. The Completions API enables you to build applications using OpenAI’s language models, like the powerful GPT-3.

Protocols/OpenAIProtocol.html#/s:6OpenAI.name: completionsStream(query:onResult:completion:)
Protocols/OpenAIProtocol.html#/s:6OpenAI.abstract: This function sends a completions query to the OpenAI API and retrieves generated completions in response. The Completions API enables you to build applications using OpenAI’s language models, like the powerful GPT-3. The result is returned by chunks.

Protocols/OpenAIProtocol.html#/s:6OpenAI.name: images(query:completion:)
Protocols/OpenAIProtocol.html#/s:6OpenAI.abstract: This function sends an images query to the OpenAI API and retrieves generated images in response. The Images Generation API enables you to create various images or graphics using OpenAI’s powerful deep learning models.

Protocols/OpenAIProtocol.html#/s:6OpenAI.name: imageEdits(query:completion:)
Protocols/OpenAIProtocol.html#/s:6OpenAI.abstract: This function sends an image edit query to the OpenAI API and retrieves generated images in response. The Images Edit API enables you to edit images or graphics using OpenAI’s powerful deep learning models.

Protocols/OpenAIProtocol.html#/s:6OpenAI.name: imageVariations(query:completion:)
Protocols/OpenAIProtocol.html#/s:6OpenAI.abstract: This function sends an image variation query to the OpenAI API and retrieves generated images in response. The Images Variations API enables you to create a variation of a given image using OpenAI’s powerful deep learning models.

Protocols/OpenAIProtocol.html#/s:6OpenAI.name: embeddings(query:completion:)
Protocols/OpenAIProtocol.html#/s:6OpenAI.abstract: This function sends an embeddings query to the OpenAI API and retrieves embeddings in response. The Embeddings API enables you to generate high-dimensional vector representations of texts, which can be used for various natural language processing tasks such as semantic similarity, clustering, and classification.

Protocols/OpenAIProtocol.html#/s:6OpenAI.name: chats(query:completion:)
Protocols/OpenAIProtocol.html#/s:6OpenAI.abstract: This function sends a chat query to the OpenAI API and retrieves chat conversation responses. The Chat API enables you to build chatbots or conversational applications using OpenAI’s powerful natural language models, like GPT-3.

Protocols/OpenAIProtocol.html#/s:6OpenAI.name: chatsStream(query:onResult:completion:)
Protocols/OpenAIProtocol.html#/s:6OpenAI.abstract: This function sends a chat query to the OpenAI API and retrieves chat stream conversation responses. The Chat API enables you to build chatbots or conversational applications using OpenAI’s powerful natural language models, like GPT-3. The result is returned by chunks.

Protocols/OpenAIProtocol.html#/s:6OpenAI.name: edits(query:completion:)
Protocols/OpenAIProtocol.html#/s:6OpenAI.abstract: This function sends an edits query to the OpenAI API and retrieves an edited version of the prompt based on the instruction given.

Protocols/OpenAIProtocol.html#/s:6OpenAI.name: model(query:completion:)
Protocols/OpenAIProtocol.html#/s:6OpenAI.abstract: This function sends a model query to the OpenAI API and retrieves a model instance, providing owner information. The Models API in this usage enables you to gather detailed information on the model in question, like GPT-3.

Protocols/OpenAIProtocol.html#/s:6OpenAI.name: models(completion:)
Protocols/OpenAIProtocol.html#/s:6OpenAI.abstract: This function sends a models query to the OpenAI API and retrieves a list of models. The Models API in this usage enables you to list all the available models.

Protocols/OpenAIProtocol.html#/s:6OpenAI.name: moderations(query:completion:)
Protocols/OpenAIProtocol.html#/s:6OpenAI.abstract: This function sends a moderations query to the OpenAI API and retrieves a list of category results to classify how text may violate OpenAI’s Content Policy.

Protocols/OpenAIProtocol.html#/s:6OpenAI.name: audioCreateSpeech(query:completion:)
Protocols/OpenAIProtocol.html#/s:6OpenAI.abstract: This function sends an AudioSpeechQuery to the OpenAI API to create audio speech from text using a specific voice and format.

Protocols/OpenAIProtocol.html#/s:6OpenAI.name: audioTranscriptions(query:completion:)
Protocols/OpenAIProtocol.html#/s:6OpenAI.abstract: Transcribes audio data using OpenAI’s audio transcription API and completes the operation asynchronously.

Protocols/OpenAIProtocol.html#/s:6OpenAI.name: audioTranslations(query:completion:)
Protocols/OpenAIProtocol.html#/s:6OpenAI.abstract: Translates audio data using OpenAI’s audio translation API and completes the operation asynchronously.

Extensions/Model.html#/s:SS6OpenAIE6gpt4.name: gpt4_o
Extensions/Model.html#/s:SS6OpenAIE6gpt4.abstract: gpt-4o, currently the most advanced, multimodal flagship model that’s cheaper and faster than GPT-4 Turbo.

Extensions/Model.html#/s:SS6OpenAIE11gpt.name: gpt4_o_mini
Extensions/Model.html#/s:SS6OpenAIE11gpt.abstract: gpt-4o-mini, currently the most affordable and intelligent model for fast and lightweight requests.

Extensions/Model.html#/s:SS6OpenAIE10gpt.name: gpt4_turbo
Extensions/Model.html#/s:SS6OpenAIE10gpt.abstract: gpt-4-turbo, The latest GPT-4 Turbo model with vision capabilities. Vision requests can now use JSON mode and function calling and more. Context window: 128,000 tokens

Extensions/Model.html#/s:SS6OpenAIE18gpt.name: gpt4_turbo_preview
Extensions/Model.html#/s:SS6OpenAIE18gpt.abstract: gpt-4-turbo, gpt-4 model with improved instruction following, JSON mode, reproducible outputs, parallel function calling and more. Maximum of 4096 output tokens

Extensions/Model.html#/s:SS6OpenAIE19gpt.name: gpt4_vision_preview
Extensions/Model.html#/s:SS6OpenAIE19gpt.abstract: gpt-4-vision-preview, able to understand images, in addition to all other GPT-4 Turbo capabilities.

Extensions/Model.html#/s:SS6OpenAIE17gpt.name: gpt4_0125_preview
Extensions/Model.html#/s:SS6OpenAIE17gpt.abstract: Snapshot of gpt-4-turbo-preview from January 25th 2024. This model reduces cases of laziness where the model doesnt complete a task. Also fixes the bug impacting non-English UTF-8 generations. Maximum of 4096 output tokens

Extensions/Model.html#/s:SS6OpenAIE17gpt.name: gpt4_1106_preview
Extensions/Model.html#/s:SS6OpenAIE17gpt.abstract: Snapshot of gpt-4-turbo-preview from November 6th 2023. Improved instruction following, JSON mode, reproducible outputs, parallel function calling and more. Maximum of 4096 output tokens

Extensions/Model.html#/s:SS6OpenAIE4gpt4.name: gpt4
Extensions/Model.html#/s:SS6OpenAIE4gpt4.abstract: Most capable gpt-4 model, outperforms any GPT-3.5 model, able to do more complex tasks, and optimized for chat.

Extensions/Model.html#/s:SS6OpenAIE9gpt4.name: gpt4_0613
Extensions/Model.html#/s:SS6OpenAIE9gpt4.abstract: Snapshot of gpt-4 from June 13th 2023 with function calling data. Unlike gpt-4, this model will not receive updates, and will be deprecated 3 months after a new version is released.

Extensions/Model.html#/s:SS6OpenAIE9gpt4.name: gpt4_0314
Extensions/Model.html#/s:SS6OpenAIE9gpt4.abstract: Snapshot of gpt-4 from March 14th 2023. Unlike gpt-4, this model will not receive updates, and will only be supported for a three month period ending on June 14th 2023.

Extensions/Model.html#/s:SS6OpenAIE8gpt4.name: gpt4_32k
Extensions/Model.html#/s:SS6OpenAIE8gpt4.abstract: Same capabilities as the base gpt-4 model but with 4x the context length. Will be updated with our latest model iteration.

Extensions/Model.html#/s:SS6OpenAIE13gpt.name: gpt4_32k_0613
Extensions/Model.html#/s:SS6OpenAIE13gpt.abstract: Snapshot of gpt-4-32k from June 13th 2023. Unlike gpt-4-32k, this model will not receive updates, and will be deprecated 3 months after a new version is released.

Extensions/Model.html#/s:SS6OpenAIE13gpt.name: gpt4_32k_0314
Extensions/Model.html#/s:SS6OpenAIE13gpt.abstract: Snapshot of gpt-4-32k from March 14th 2023. Unlike gpt-4-32k, this model will not receive updates, and will only be supported for a three month period ending on June 14th 2023.

Extensions/Model.html#/s:SS6OpenAIE11gpt.name: gpt3_5Turbo
Extensions/Model.html#/s:SS6OpenAIE11gpt.abstract: Most capable gpt-3.5-turbo model and optimized for chat. Will be updated with our latest model iteration.

Extensions/Model.html#/s:SS6OpenAIE16gpt.name: gpt3_5Turbo_0125
Extensions/Model.html#/s:SS6OpenAIE16gpt.abstract: Snapshot of gpt-3.5-turbo from January 25th 2024. Decreased prices by 50%. Various improvements including higher accuracy at responding in requested formats and a fix for a bug which caused a text encoding issue for non-English language function calls.

Extensions/Model.html#/s:SS6OpenAIE16gpt.name: gpt3_5Turbo_1106
Extensions/Model.html#/s:SS6OpenAIE16gpt.abstract: Snapshot of gpt-3.5-turbo from November 6th 2023. The latest gpt-3.5-turbo model with improved instruction following, JSON mode, reproducible outputs, parallel function calling and more.

Extensions/Model.html#/s:SS6OpenAIE16gpt.name: gpt3_5Turbo_0613
Extensions/Model.html#/s:SS6OpenAIE16gpt.abstract: Snapshot of gpt-3.5-turbo from June 13th 2023 with function calling data. Unlike gpt-3.5-turbo, this model will not receive updates, and will be deprecated 3 months after a new version is released.

Extensions/Model.html#/s:SS6OpenAIE16gpt.name: gpt3_5Turbo_0301
Extensions/Model.html#/s:SS6OpenAIE16gpt.abstract: Snapshot of gpt-3.5-turbo from March 1st 2023. Unlike gpt-3.5-turbo, this model will not receive updates, and will only be supported for a three month period ending on June 1st 2023.

Extensions/Model.html#/s:SS6OpenAIE15gpt.name: gpt3_5Turbo_16k
Extensions/Model.html#/s:SS6OpenAIE15gpt.abstract: Same capabilities as the standard gpt-3.5-turbo model but with 4 times the context.

Extensions/Model.html#/s:SS6OpenAIE20gpt.name: gpt3_5Turbo_16k_0613
Extensions/Model.html#/s:SS6OpenAIE20gpt.abstract: Snapshot of gpt-3.5-turbo-16k from June 13th 2023. Unlike gpt-3.5-turbo-16k, this model will not receive updates, and will be deprecated 3 months after a new version is released.

Extensions/Model.html#/s:SS6OpenAIE15tex.name: textDavinci_003
Extensions/Model.html#/s:SS6OpenAIE15tex.abstract: Can do any language task with better quality, longer output, and consistent instruction-following than the curie, babbage, or ada models. Also supports inserting completions within text.

Extensions/Model.html#/s:SS6OpenAIE15tex.name: textDavinci_002
Extensions/Model.html#/s:SS6OpenAIE15tex.abstract: Similar capabilities to text-davinci-003 but trained with supervised fine-tuning instead of reinforcement learning.

Extensions/Model.html#/s:SS6OpenAIE9text.name: textCurie
Extensions/Model.html#/s:SS6OpenAIE9text.abstract: Very capable, faster and lower cost than Davinci.

Extensions/Model.html#/s:SS6OpenAIE11tex.name: textBabbage
Extensions/Model.html#/s:SS6OpenAIE11tex.abstract: Capable of straightforward tasks, very fast, and lower cost.

Extensions/Model.html#/s:SS6OpenAIE7text.name: textAda
Extensions/Model.html#/s:SS6OpenAIE7text.abstract: Capable of very simple tasks, usually the fastest model in the GPT-3 series, and lowest cost.

Extensions/Model.html#/s:SS6OpenAIE5tts_.name: tts_1
Extensions/Model.html#/s:SS6OpenAIE5tts_.abstract: The latest text to speech model, optimized for speed.

Extensions/Model.html#/s:SS6OpenAIE8tts_.name: tts_1_hd
Extensions/Model.html#/s:SS6OpenAIE8tts_.abstract: The latest text to speech model, optimized for quality.

Extensions/Model.html#/s:SS6OpenAIE7davi.name: davinci
Extensions/Model.html#/s:SS6OpenAIE7davi.abstract: Most capable GPT-3 model. Can do any task the other models can do, often with higher quality.

Extensions/Model.html#/s:SS6OpenAIE5curi.name: curie
Extensions/Model.html#/s:SS6OpenAIE5curi.abstract: Very capable, but faster and lower cost than Davinci.

Extensions/Model.html#/s:SS6OpenAIE7babb.name: babbage
Extensions/Model.html#/s:SS6OpenAIE7babb.abstract: Capable of straightforward tasks, very fast, and lower cost.

Extensions/Model.html#/s:SS6OpenAIE3adaS.name: ada
Extensions/Model.html#/s:SS6OpenAIE3adaS.abstract: Capable of very simple tasks, usually the fastest model in the GPT-3 series, and lowest cost.

Extensions/Model.html#/s:SS6OpenAIE20tex.name: textModerationStable
Extensions/Model.html#/s:SS6OpenAIE20tex.abstract: Almost as capable as the latest model, but slightly older.

Extensions/Model.html#/s:SS6OpenAIE20tex.name: textModerationLatest
Extensions/Model.html#/s:SS6OpenAIE20tex.abstract: Most capable moderation model. Accuracy will be slightly higher than the stable model.

Classes/OpenAI/Configuration.html#/s:6Op.name: host
Classes/OpenAI/Configuration.html#/s:6Op.abstract: API host. Set this property if you use some kind of proxy or your own server. Default is api.openai.com

Typealiases.html.name: Type Aliases
Typealiases.html.abstract: The following type aliases are available globally.
